the \"Speedmaster\" selected by the National Aeronautics and Space Administration was used in the Apollo program and in 1969 won the honor of being the first wristwatch to land on the moon.

Seiko Coutura Solar Chronograph Radio-Sync Solar World Time 44.5mm Stainless Steel SSG009




World time technology meets fashion-forward design in this Coutura Radio-Sync Solar Chronograph watch from Seiko. Crafted in stainless steel, this quality timepiece features a 44.5mm case, black dial, LumiBrite hands, chronograph sub-dials, date display, blue accents, and second hand. Setting a new standard, the bezel displays 25 time zones. The stylish link bracelet secures with a deployment clasp. The accurate solar quartz movement takes its energy from light and stores it in a self-charging battery that never needs to be changed. Water-resistant to 100 metres, this wristwatch includes a three-year limited manufacturer's warranty. Radio Sync Solar World Time Chronograph technology offers the precision of one second every 100,000 years.




Radio Sync Solar Chronograph




Radio-controlled: Automatically receives radio signals to precisely adjust the time and calendar




Powered by light energy- no battery change required




Signal reception and result indicator




World time function (25 time zones)




24 hour indicator




6-month power reserve




Power save function




Chronograph measures up to 60 minutes in 1/5 second increments with split time measurement function




Date calendar




LumiBrite hands and markers




Screwdown crown




Glass caseback




Sapphire crystal




Case diameter: 44.5mm




Stainless steel case and bracelet




Cabochon crown




Water-resistant to 10 bar, 100 meters (330 feet)

This rare Speedmaster features a striking silver dial that is decorated with gold accents from the hands, numeral markers and complication outlines. A contrasting 18K yellow gold tachymetre bezel sits upon a 40mm stainless steel casebody, which is attached to a matching stainless-steel bracelet. All powered by the Omega Calibre 1164 automatic movement.

The chronograph has always featured prominently in the vast range of complications in which Patek Philippe has demonstrated its virtuosity. For over 175 years, the manufacture has created a wealth of different models, many of which count among the timepieces most admired and sought after by connoisseurs and collectors. Self-winding mechanical movement. Caliber CH 28‑520 IRM QA 24H. Flyback chronograph. Annual Calendar. Matte blue opaline, 8 baguette diamond hour markers (~0.23 ct). Platinum case. Sapphire crystal case back. Water-resistant to 30 m. Case diameter: 40.5 mm. Height: 13.53 mm. Bezel set with 36 baguette diamonds (~3.48 ct). Fold-over clasp set with 22 baguette diamonds (~0.97 ct). Alligator strap with square scales, hand-stitched, shiny navy blue. Fold-over clasp.
